summary: An Ordinance providing for the laying off, extending and establishing of North Sixty-seventh Street, from Dayton Avenue to Phinney Avenue, all in the City of Seattle, as a public street and highway; and providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor; and providing that the payment of the cost of said improvement be made by special assessment upon the property specially benefited, in the manner provided by law.
